# Row-wise Operations

Unfortunately, based on [this issue](https://github.com/HenrikBengtsson/matrixStats/issues/238), rowwise computations are not easy to be speeded in matrixStats. So further benchmarking will drop it.


::: {.cell hash='index_cache/html/bench-rowwise_bb62e567bba7d5aeee779bb207253c0d'}

```{.r .cell-code}
bench <- bench::press(
  nrow = c(10, 100, 1000),
  ncol = c(100, 1000, 10000),
  {
    data <- matrix(rnorm(nrow * ncol), nrow = nrow)
    vec <- rnorm(ncol)
    bench::mark(
      collapse = data %r-% vec,
      Rfast = Rfast::eachrow(data, vec, "-"),
      base = data - rep(vec, each = nrow)
    )
  }
)
```
:::

::: {.cell .column-page hash='index_cache/html/fig-rowwise_348d5381166e9782f19dd41e524b360e'}

```{.r .cell-code}
plot(bench)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![Benchmark of row-wise operations](index_files/figure-html/fig-rowwise-1.png){#fig-rowwise width=768}
:::
:::


# Scale


::: {.cell hash='index_cache/html/bench-scale_35ee548f136868a7320f3f72fddf369b'}

```{.r .cell-code}
fscale_rfast <- function(x) {
  means <- Rfast::colmeans(x)
  sds <- Rfast::colVars(x, std = TRUE)
  Rfast::eachrow(
    Rfast::eachrow(x, means, "-"),
    sds, "/"
  )
}
bench <- bench::press(
  nrow = c(10, 100, 1000),
  ncol = c(100, 1000, 10000),
  {
    data <- matrix(rnorm(nrow * ncol), nrow = nrow)
    bench::mark(
      collapse = fscale(data),
      Rfast = fscale_rfast(data),
      base = scale(data),
      check = FALSE # base scale will add attributes
    )
  }
)
```
:::

::: {.cell .column-page hash='index_cache/html/fig-scale_2c46a157a697625c33e60eb05adf5b3d'}

```{.r .cell-code}
plot(bench)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![Benchmark of scale](index_files/figure-html/fig-scale-1.png){#fig-scale width=768}
:::
:::


# Conclusion

From the above figures, we will find Rfast is the fastest package for matrix operations. Previously, I have used collapse package, which is actually fast enough. But now I will switch to Rfast.
